label: ESCHO
description:
Danish composer Astrid Sonne opens up her heart on 'Great Doubt', singing candidly for the first time over powdery beats and jerky instrumentation (assisted by none other than Slauson Malone, Ben Vince, Levitation Orchestra's Emma Barnaby and Alvilda Reiter Jakobsen), and even referencing Mariah Carey. It's a revelation - and funny in places too - properly in line with Tirzah, ML Buch and HTRK.

label: Worldwide Unlimited / True Panther
description:
One of UK Grime’s most shadowy figures comes of age with a killer full length debut released in collab between True Panther and DJ Python’s Worldwide Unlimited, brimming with an incandescent energy arcing from OG to contemporary eras. It's fully addictive gear, joining unexpected dots between hook-heavy pop and weirder modes, on a tip somewhere between Vegyn, Dean Blunt, Playboi Carti, Klein & Junior Boys - just v v good!!!!

RE:LAX
description:
London club catalyst re:ni shells a stark first 12” on her and Laksa’s re:lax label after rude drops for Ilian Tape and Batu’s Timedance

Some five years since they broke thru with a split tape on Beneath’s No Symbols, UK -based producer Lauren Bush aka re:ni is in cold possession of a distinctively brittle, bullish sort of hardcore hard drum sound, as steadily firmed up with the ‘Revenge Body’ 12” for Ilian Tape and 2024’s ‘BeautySick’ EP on Batu’s label.
